sentences: Kharesma Ravichandran (born 8 May 2000) is a British playback singer for Tamil cinema films.
A professionally trained western vocalist, Ravichandran began her playback singing career in 2014, with her debut coming in the Tamil film Yennai Arindhaal (2015).

In 2011, Kharesma moved to India where she began learning Hindustani and Carnatic music.
Since then, she was nominated for the 63rd Filmfare - Best Female Singer Award, SIIMA 2016 for Best Playback singer and Edison Awards 2016.
In January 2020, she released her first single "Marandhitiyo", which featured Paul B Salius and MadPanda, from her upcoming EP under the Underground Tribe label led by Hiphop Tamizha.
She is currently signed as an independent artist under Hiphop Tamizha’s label “Underground”.
